def: The forests or partly cleared grounds on the frontiers.
The state of being on an equality, as in rank or power.
One who lacks or is in want.
A public sale of anything, by outcry, to the highest bidder; anauction. [Obsoles.] Vendue master, one who is authorized to sell anyproperty by vendue; an auctioneer. [Obsoles.]
More recent than the Paleozoic, -- that is, including theMesozoic and Cenozoic.
A descendant of Benjamin; one of the tribe of Benjamin. Judg.iii. 15.

A liliaceous plant of the genus Allium (A.cepa), having astrong-flavored bulb and long hollow leaves; also, its bulbous root,much used as an article of food. The name is often extended to otherspecies of the genus. Onion fish (Zoöl.), the grenadier.-- Onion fly (Zoöl.) a dipterous insect whose larva feeds upon theonion; especially, Anthomyia ceparum and Ortalis flexa.-- Welsh onion. (Bot.) See Cibol.-- Wild onion (Bot.), a name given to several species of the genusAllium.
Toward, or in the direction of, the east.
